        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 25 at 9:31PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 930 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of Hartley, or 10 miles southeast of Dalhart, moving
northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of southwestern
Sherman, southeastern Dallam and northeastern Hartley Counties.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 100 AM CDT for
the Panhandle of Texas.</instruction>
